The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, January 07, 2004  Business Briefs																								 Mumbai, Jan. 6: Centurion Bank has appointed Shailendra Bhandari as its chief executive officer. Bhandari will be responsible for coordinating all business and market development activities and will provide overall leadership for managing the operations of the bank. Bhandari left Prudential ICICI Management Company to join Centurion Bank. 																								 New Delhi, Jan. 6: The long-awaited umbrella legislation for special economic zones providing for a liberalised labour regime and tax incentives is likely to get cabinets nod on Wednesday. With the Lok Sabha session expected to be convened in a couple of weeks for passage of vote-on-account, the comprehensive SEZ legislation could be introduced during the brief session.																								 Mumbai, Jan. 6: Bank of India (BoI) will issue Tier-II bonds for raising Rs 350 crore to shore up its capital adequacy base. The BoI bonds Series-V would have a 120-month tenor.																								 New Delhi, Jan. 6: Samtel Color has posted a marginally lower net profit of Rs 8.11 crore for the quarter ended December 2003 on a 6 per cent higher turnover of Rs 270.81 crore. The company had posted Rs 8.56 crore net profit in the same quarter last year on a Rs 254.34-crore turnover.																								 New Delhi, Jan. 6: The government today said foodgrain agents will be exempt from service tax as they did not fall under the category of clearing and forwarding agent services.
